{"id":1019736822,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"3Â months","timestamp":1691894472,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/1019736822/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Double a Number Represented as a Linked List","memory":"N/A","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * struct ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode *next;\n *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}\n *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}\n *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    ListNode* doubleIt(ListNode* head) {\n        ListNode* l1=head;\n        ListNode* l2=head;\n         ListNode* dummy = new ListNode(-1);\n        ListNode* ans = dummy;\n        int carry = 0, sum = 0;\n        while (l1 || l2 || carry) {\n            sum = carry;\n            if (l1) {\n                sum += l1->val;\n                l1 = l1->next;\n            }\n            if (l2) {\n                sum += l2->val;\n                l2 = l2->next;\n            }\n            carry = sum / 10;\n            dummy->next = new ListNode(sum % 10);\n            dummy = dummy->next;\n        }\n        return ans->next;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"double-a-number-represented-as-a-linked-list","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
